WEBVTT

00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:30.200
use credit cards a lot, but do

00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:34.240
they know how credit cards make money?

00:02:34.240 --> 00:02:36.160
Merchants charge fees.

00:02:36.160 --> 00:02:37.320
I guess they make

00:02:37.320 --> 00:02:39.840
money from people who can't pay back their debts.

00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:42.840
Another way is to make money from merchants' cooperation fees.

00:02:42.880 --> 00:02:47.360
It seems that colleagues have a vague understanding of credit cards.

00:02:47.360 --> 00:02:48.720
Fortunately,

00:02:48.720 --> 00:02:52.080
to understand the operating mechanism of credit cards, it's

00:02:52.080 --> 00:02:53.960
nothing more than one word:

00:02:53.960 --> 00:02:55.280
"trust", which is

00:02:55.280 --> 00:02:58.560
credit in English.

